snippet: The N.F.C. championship game between Seattle and San Francisco is the latest event in a long-running debate over football and cultural superiority in the West Coast cities.
abstract: NFC championship game between Seattle Seahawks and San Francisco 49ers is the latest event in a long-running debate over football and cultural superiority in the West Coast cities; teams act like NFL's fiercest rivals and tension’s origins trace to five years ago, when both teams were bad and their current coaches, Pete Carroll and Jim Harbaugh, led college programs.
lead_paragraph: The N.F.C. championship game between Seattle and San Francisco is the latest event in a long-running debate over football and cultural superiority in the West Coast cities.

headline.main: Rivalry Between Seattle and San Francisco Heats Up the West Coast
headline.print_headline: In College Grudge, Roots of Newly Heated Rivalry
